{"title_page": "Morgan Lamoisson", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Morgan Lamoisson\n| image          = Denain - Grand Prix de Denain, le 17 avril 2014 (A252).JPG\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Lamoisson at the 2014 [[Grand Prix de Denain]]\n| fullname       = Morgan Lamoisson\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=y|1988|9|7}}\n| birth_place    = [[Issoudun]], France\n| height         = 1.78 m\n| weight         = 69 kg\n| currentteam    = Retired\n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = [[Cycling sprinter|Sprinter]]\n| amateuryears1  = 2007\u20132010\n| amateurteam1   = Blois CAC 41\n| amateuryears2  = 2011\u20132012\n| amateurteam2   = [[Vend\u00e9e U]]\n| amateuryears3  = 2016\n| amateurteam3   = [[Vend\u00e9e U]]\n| proyears1      = 2013\u20132015\n| proteam1       = {{ct|EUC|2013}}<ref>http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Morgan_Lamoisson</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://62.50.72.82/UCIBWS/(S(3rxqschpfw4p3qchmh3rrhwc))/Teams/detail/en/ROA/3010|title=Team Europcar (EUC)&nbsp;\u2013 FRA|accessdate=2 January 2014|work=[[UCI World Tour]] | publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]}}</ref>\n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n}}\n\n'''Morgan Lamoisson''' (born 7 September 1988 in [[Issoudun]]) is a French former cyclist, who rode professionally between 2013 and 2015 for the {{ct|EUC|2015}} team. Lamoisson retired at the end of the 2016 season, after a season with amateur team Vend\u00e9e U.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.directvelo.com/actualite/53840/la-derniere-recolte-de-morgan-lamoisson|title=La derni\u00e8re r\u00e9colte de Morgan Lamoisson|language=French|trans-title=The last harvest of Morgan Lamoisson|work=Directvelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|first=Dominique|last=Turgis|date=2 October 2016|accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n;2011\n: 1st Stage 3 [[Tour du Loir-et-Cher]]\n: 6th [[La Roue Tourangelle]]\n;2012\n: 4th [[Val d'Ille Classic]]\n;2014\n: 5th [[Ch\u00e2teauroux Classic]]\n: 7th Overall [[Tour de l'Eurom\u00e9tropole]]\n;2015\n: 6th [[Duo Normand]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{stack|{{Commons category|Morgan Lamoisson}}}}\n* {{Cycling Archives}}\n* {{CQ ranking}}\n* {{ProCyclingStats}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lamoisson, Morgan}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Issoudun]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Indre]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Morgan Lamoisson\n| image          = Denain - Grand Prix de Denain, le 17 avril 2014 (A252).JPG\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = Lamoisson at the 2014 [[Grand Prix de Denain]]\n| fullname       = Morgan Lamoisson\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=y|1988|9|7}}\n| birth_place    = [[Issoudun]], France\n| height         = 1.78 m\n| weight         = 69 kg\n| currentteam    = Retired\n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = [[Cycling sprinter|Sprinter]]\n| amateuryears1  = 2007\u20132010\n| amateurteam1   = Blois CAC 41\n| amateuryears2  = 2011\u20132012\n| amateurteam2   = [[Vend\u00e9e U]]\n| amateuryears3  = 2016\n| amateurteam3   = [[Vend\u00e9e U]]\n| proyears1      = 2013\u20132015\n| proteam1       = {{ct|EUC|2013}}<ref>http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Morgan_Lamoisson</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://62.50.72.82/UCIBWS/(S(3rxqschpfw4p3qchmh3rrhwc))/Teams/detail/en/ROA/3010|title=Team Europcar (EUC)&nbsp;\u2013 FRA|accessdate=2 January 2014|work=[[UCI World Tour]] | publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]}}</ref>\n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n}}\n\n'''Morgan Lamoisson''' (born 7 September 1988 in [[Issoudun]]) is a French former cyclist, who rode professionally between 2013 and 2015 for the {{ct|EUC|2015}} team. Lamoisson retired at the end of the 2016 season, after a season with amateur team Vend\u00e9e U.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.directvelo.com/actualite/53840/la-derniere-recolte-de-morgan-lamoisson|title=La derni\u00e8re r\u00e9colte de Morgan Lamoisson|language=French|trans-title=The last harvest of Morgan Lamoisson|work=Directvelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|first=Dominique|last=Turgis|date=2 October 2016|accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n;2011\n: 1st Stage 3 [[Tour du Loir-et-Cher]]\n: 6th [[La Roue Tourangelle]]\n;2012\n: 4th [[Val d'Ille Classic]]\n;2014\n: 5th [[Ch\u00e2teauroux Classic]]\n: 7th Overall [[Tour de l'Eurom\u00e9tropole]]\n;2015\n: 6th [[Duo Normand]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{stack|{{Commons category|Morgan Lamoisson}}}}\n* {{Cycling Archives}}\n* {{CQ ranking}}\n* {{ProCyclingStats}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lamoisson, Morgan}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Issoudun]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Indre]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1980s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgan_Lamoisson"}
{"title_page": "Flag of Slovakia", "text_new": "{{Infobox flag\n| Name = Slovakia\n| Article = \n| Image = Flag of Slovakia.svg\n| Nickname = \n| Morenicks = \n| Use = 111000 \n| Symbol =\n| Proportion = 2:3\n| Adoption = {{Start date and age|1992|09|03|df=yes}}\n| Design = A horizontal [[tricolor (flag)|tricolor]] of white, blue, and red; charged with [[Coat of arms of Slovakia|coat of arms]] at the [[hoist (flag)|hoist side]]\n| Designer = [[Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik]]<ref name=teraz/><br>[[Ladislav Vrtel]]<ref name=teraz>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Zomrel autor v\u00fdtvarn\u00e9ho spracovania \u0161t\u00e1tnych symbolov SR |url=http://www.teraz.sk/slovensko/zomrel-autor-vytvarneho-spracovania-symb/273523-clanok.html |work=[[News Agency of the Slovak Republic]] |publisher= |date=2017-08-03 |accessdate=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n| Image2 = Flag of Slovakia (1939\u20131945).svg\n| Use2 = 100100 \n| Symbol2 =\n| Proportion2 = 2:3\n| Adoption2 = {{Start date and age|1939|03|14|df=yes}}\n| Design2 = A horizontal [[tricolor (flag)|tricolor]] of white, blue, and red\n}}\n[[File:Flag of Slovakia vertical (gabbe).jpg|thumb|right|When flown vertically the coat of arms is rotated. This is the reverse side.]]\n\nThe current form of the [[national flag|national]] '''flag of Slovakia''' ({{lang-sk|Vlajka Slovenska}}) was adopted by [[Slovakia]]'s [[Constitution of Slovakia|Constitution]], which came into force on 3 September 1992. The flag, in common with many other flags of [[Slavs|Slavic]] nations, uses [[Pan-Slavic colors]] \u2013 [[red]], [[white]] and [[blue]].\n\n==History==\nSlovakia's flag in its current form (but with another coat of arms on it or without any arms) can be dated back to the revolutionary year 1848{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}} (see: ''[[The Revolutions of 1848 in the Habsburg areas]]''). It was also used semi-officially in [[Czechoslovakia]] before [[World War II]], by the [[Slovak Republic (1939-1945)|Slovak Republic]] during [[World War II]].\n\nIn 1990, the Interior Ministry tasked [[Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik]], a painter and heraldic artist, and [[Ladislav Vrtel]], an expert in heraldry, with creating a new coat of arms and national flag.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Zomrel autor slovensk\u00fdch n\u00e1rodn\u00fdch symbolov Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik ml. |url=https://domov.sme.sk/c/20618149/zomrel-autor-slovenskych-narodnych-symbolov-ladislav-cisarik-ml.html |work=[[SME (newspaper)|SME]] |publisher= |date=2017-08-03 |accessdate=2017-09-06}}</ref><ref name=ssp>{{cite news |first=Marcela|last=Glevick\u00e1|title=How the national emblem appeared \u2013 including so far secret communism designs |url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/20460586/how-the-national-emblem-appeared-including-so-far-secret-communism-designs.html |work=[[The Slovak Spectator]] |publisher= |date=2017-02-16 |accessdate=2017-09-07}}</ref> \u010cis\u00e1rik and Vrtel based their designs for a modern coat of arms and flag on an existing 14th Century coat of arms.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/> However, \u010cis\u00e1rik and Vrtel chose to enlarge the double cross three times to emphasize it as a national symbol.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/> In addition to the national coat of arms and the national flag, the duo also designed a new presidential standard, which incorporates the double cross as well.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/>\n\nThe new flag was finally adopted (initially without \u010cis\u00e1rik's and Vrtel's coat of arms) on 1 March 1990 as the flag of the Slovak Republic within Czechoslovakia. The coat of arms was added on 3 September 1992 and a special law describing the details of the flag followed in February 1993.\n\n==Design==\nSince the Slovak flag without the coat of arms is identical to the current [[Flag of Russia|flag of the Russian Federation]], and can also be compared to the modern [[flag of Slovenia]], the [[Constitution of Slovakia]] added the [[Coat of arms of Slovakia|national coat of arms]] in September 1992.\n\n==Flags==\n\n===Historical flags===\n<gallery>\nFile:Nitrianska_vlajka.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Flag of the [[Principality of Nitra]]\nFile:Slovensk\u00e1_vlajka_1848.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Slovak flag proposed by the [[Demands of the Slovak Nation|Demands of the Slovak nation]]\nFile:SlovenskaVlajka1848.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}One of more flags used by slovak volunteers during [[Slovak Uprising 1848-1849|Slovak Uprising 1848]]. Flags from this period introduced blue color into the slovak flag for first time, after [[Slavic Congress of Prague|Slavic Congress]]. Used also as flag of [[Slovak National Council (1848\u201349)|Slovak National Council (1848-49)]]\nFile:Slovensk%C3%A1_vlajka_1849.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Another flag used during the [[Slovak Uprising of 1848\u201349|Slovak Uprising]]\nFile:Slovensk\u00e1_vlajka_1848_z.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Another flag used during the [[Slovak Uprising of 1848\u201349|Slovak Uprising]]. Basically historical flag of Hungary with green replaced by blue. The first depiction of the hills in coat of arms in blue color\nFile:Red flag.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Flag of the [[Slovak Soviet Republic]]\nFile:Flag of Czechoslovakia.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}[[Flag of Czechoslovakia]] (1920\u20131992)\nFile:Flag of First Slovak Republic 1939-1945.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Oficial flag of Slovaks adopted in 1868, but used also before. Later adopted as the official flag of the autonomous Slovak land within the [[Second Czechoslovak Republic]] (1938\u20131939), [[Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)|WWII Slovak Republic]] (1939\u20131945) and [[Slovak Republic]] within Czechoslovakia (1990\u20131992)\nFile:War ensign of the First Slovak Republic.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}War Ensign of the Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)\n</gallery>\n\n===Presidential standard===\n<gallery>\nFile:Flag of the President of Slovakia (1939-1945).svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Standard of the President (1939\u20131945)\nFile:Flag of the President of Slovakia.svg|Standard of the President (1993\u2013present)\n</gallery>\n\n===Other flags===\n<gallery>\nFile:Flag of Slovakia vertical.svg|Vertical version of the flag of Slovakia\nFile:Flag of Slovakia, construction sheet.png|Construction sheet\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Coat of arms of Slovakia]]\n*[[Pan-Slavic colors]]\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{sister|project=commons|text=[[Wikimedia Commons]] has media related to '''''[[Commons:Category:Flags of Slovakia|Flags of Slovakia]]'''''}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110129052109/http://www.slovakiacompany.com/slovakia-guide/slovakia-flag.html Slovakia Flag]\n* [http://www.zbierka.sk/zz/predpisy/default.aspx?PredpisID=12478&FileName=93-z063&Rocnik=1993 Z\u00e1kon NR SR o \u0161t\u00e1tnych symboloch Slovenskej republiky a ich pou\u017e\u00edvan\u00ed]\n\n{{Clear}}\n{{Slovakia topics}}\n{{Flag of Europe}}\n{{nationalflags}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Slovakia, Flag of}}\n[[Category:Flags with crosses]]\n[[Category:Flags introduced in 1992]]\n[[Category:National symbols of Slovakia|Flag]]\n[[Category:National flags]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox flag\n| Name = Slovakia\n| Article = \n| Image = Flag of Slovakia.svg\n| Nickname = \n| Morenicks = \n| Use = 111000 \n| Symbol =\n| Proportion = 2:3\n| Adoption = {{Start date and age|1992|09|03|df=yes}}\n| Design = A horizontal [[tricolor (flag)|tricolor]] of white, blue, and red; charged with [[Coat of arms of Slovakia|coat of arms]] at the [[hoist (flag)|hoist side]]\n| Designer = [[Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik]]<ref name=teraz/><br>[[Ladislav Vrtel]]<ref name=teraz>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Zomrel autor v\u00fdtvarn\u00e9ho spracovania \u0161t\u00e1tnych symbolov SR |url=http://www.teraz.sk/slovensko/zomrel-autor-vytvarneho-spracovania-symb/273523-clanok.html |work=[[News Agency of the Slovak Republic]] |publisher= |date=2017-08-03 |accessdate=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n| Image2 = Flag of Slovakia (1939\u20131945).svg\n| Use2 = 100100 \n| Symbol2 =\n| Proportion2 = 2:3\n| Adoption2 = {{Start date and age|1939|03|14|df=yes}}\n| Design2 = A horizontal [[tricolor (flag)|tricolor]] of white, blue, and red\n}}\n[[File:Flag of Slovakia vertical (gabbe).jpg|thumb|right|When flown vertically the coat of arms is rotated. This is the reverse side.]]\n\nThe current form of the [[national flag|national]] '''flag of Slovakia''' ({{lang-sk|Vlajka Slovenska}}) was adopted by [[Slovakia]]'s [[Constitution of Slovakia|Constitution]], which came into force on 3 September 1992. The flag, in common with many other flags of [[Slavs|Slavic]] nations, uses [[Pan-Slavic colors]] \u2013 [[red]], [[white]] and [[blue]].\n\n==History==\nSlovakia's flag in its current form (but with another coat of arms on it or without any arms) can be dated back to the revolutionary year 1848{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}} (see: ''[[The Revolutions of 1848 in the Habsburg areas]]''). It was also used semi-officially in [[Czechoslovakia]] before [[World War II]], by the [[Slovak Republic (1939-1945)|Slovak Republic]] during [[World War II]].\n\nIn 1990, the Interior Ministry tasked [[Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik]], a painter and heraldic artist, and [[Ladislav Vrtel]], an expert in heraldry, with creating a new coat of arms and national flag.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Zomrel autor slovensk\u00fdch n\u00e1rodn\u00fdch symbolov Ladislav \u010cis\u00e1rik ml. |url=https://domov.sme.sk/c/20618149/zomrel-autor-slovenskych-narodnych-symbolov-ladislav-cisarik-ml.html |work=[[SME (newspaper)|SME]] |publisher= |date=2017-08-03 |accessdate=2017-09-06}}</ref><ref name=ssp>{{cite news |first=Marcela|last=Glevick\u00e1|title=How the national emblem appeared \u2013 including so far secret communism designs |url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/20460586/how-the-national-emblem-appeared-including-so-far-secret-communism-designs.html |work=[[The Slovak Spectator]] |publisher= |date=2017-02-16 |accessdate=2017-09-07}}</ref> \u010cis\u00e1rik and Vrtel based their designs for a modern coat of arms and flag on an existing 14th Century coat of arms.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/> However, \u010cis\u00e1rik and Vrtel chose to enlarge the double cross three times to emphasize it as a national symbol.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/> In addition to the national coat of arms and the national flag, the duo also designed a new presidential standard, which incorporates the double cross as well.<ref name=teraz/><ref name=sme/>\n\nThe new flag was finally adopted (initially without \u010cis\u00e1rik's and Vrtel's coat of arms) on 1 March 1990 as the flag of the Slovak Republic within Czechoslovakia. The coat of arms was added on 3 September 1992 and a special law describing the details of the flag followed in February 1993.\n\n==Design==\nSince the Slovak flag without the coat of arms is identical to the current [[Flag of Russia|flag of the Russian Federation]], and can also be compared to the modern [[flag of Slovenia]], the [[Constitution of Slovakia]] added the [[Coat of arms of Slovakia|national coat of arms]] in September 1992.\n\n==Flags==\n\n===Historical flags===\n<gallery>\nFile:Nitrianska_vlajka.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Flag of the [[Principality of Nitra]]\nFile:Slovensk\u00e1_vlajka_1848.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Slovak flag proposed by the [[Demands of the Slovak Nation|Demands of the Slovak nation]]\nFile:SlovenskaVlajka1848.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}One of more flags used by slovak volunteers during [[Slovak Uprising 1848-1849|Slovak Uprising 1848]]. Flags from this period introduced blue color into the slovak flag for first time, after [[Slavic Congress of Prague|Slavic Congress]]. Used also as flag of [[Slovak National Council (1848\u201349)|Slovak National Council (1848-49)]]\nFile:Slovensk%C3%A1_vlajka_1849.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Another flag used during the [[Slovak Uprising of 1848\u201349|Slovak Uprising]]\nFile:Slovensk\u00e1_vlajka_1848_z.png|{{FIAV|historical|}}Another flag used during the [[Slovak Uprising of 1848\u201349|Slovak Uprising]]. Basically historical flag of Hungary with green replaced by blue. The first depiction of the hills in coat of arms in blue color\nFile:Red flag.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Flag of the [[Slovak Soviet Republic]]\nFile:Flag of Czechoslovakia.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}[[Flag of Czechoslovakia]] (1920\u20131992)\nFile:Flag of First Slovak Republic 1939-1945.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Oficial flag of Slovaks adopted in 1868, but used also before. Later adopted as the ffficial flag of the autonomous Slovak land within the [[Second Czechoslovak Republic]] (1938\u20131939), [[Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)|WWII Slovak Republic]] (1939\u20131945) and [[Slovak Republic]] within Czechoslovakia (1990\u20131992)\nFile:War ensign of the First Slovak Republic.svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}War Ensign of the Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)\n</gallery>\n\n===Presidential standard===\n<gallery>\nFile:Flag of the President of Slovakia (1939-1945).svg|{{FIAV|historical|}}Standard of the President (1939\u20131945)\nFile:Flag of the President of Slovakia.svg|Standard of the President (1993\u2013present)\n</gallery>\n\n===Other flags===\n<gallery>\nFile:Flag of Slovakia vertical.svg|Vertical version of the flag of Slovakia\nFile:Flag of Slovakia, construction sheet.png|Construction sheet\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Coat of arms of Slovakia]]\n*[[Pan-Slavic colors]]\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{sister|project=commons|text=[[Wikimedia Commons]] has media related to '''''[[Commons:Category:Flags of Slovakia|Flags of Slovakia]]'''''}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110129052109/http://www.slovakiacompany.com/slovakia-guide/slovakia-flag.html Slovakia Flag]\n* [http://www.zbierka.sk/zz/predpisy/default.aspx?PredpisID=12478&FileName=93-z063&Rocnik=1993 Z\u00e1kon NR SR o \u0161t\u00e1tnych symboloch Slovenskej republiky a ich pou\u017e\u00edvan\u00ed]\n\n{{Clear}}\n{{Slovakia topics}}\n{{Flag of Europe}