{"title_page": "Moana Moo-Caille", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| headercolor    = \n| name           = Moana Moo Caille\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = French\n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = \n| birth_place    = \n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Cycling]]\n| event          = [[Bicycle motocross|BMX]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| club           = \n| team           = \n| turnedpro      = \n| coach          = \n| retired        = \n| coaching       = \n| worlds         = \n| regionals      = \n| nationals      = \n| olympics       = \n| paralympics    = \n| highestranking = \n| pb             = \n| show-medals    = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Moana Moo Caille''' (13 August 1988, [[Le Port-Marly]]) is a French racing [[cyclist]] who represents France in [[BMX]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mo/moana-moo-caille-1.html|title=Moana Moo-Caille Bio, Stats, and Results|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-01}}</ref> He competed in the [[Cycling at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's BMX|men's BMX]] event at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"london2012\">{{cite web|url=http://www.london2012.com/cycling-bmx/event/men-bmx/|title=Men's BMX Racing|work=[[2012 Summer Olympics]]|publisher=London2012.com|accessdate=August 6, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121204180049/http://www.london2012.com/cycling-bmx/event/men-bmx/|archivedate=4 December 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moo-Caille, Moana}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclis